---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout>
  <section class="pt-[25vh] pb-12 px-6 max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">PleXion Framework</h1>
    <p class="text-lg mb-4">
      PleXion is a powerful, modular Java framework built to rival Spring — but with less magic and more explicit architecture.
      It’s clean, extensible, and built for developers who want full control.
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-3">
      <li>Modular core with plugin lifecycle hooks</li>
      <li>Custom class loader with secure .jar scanning</li>
      <li>Built-in REST support (Undertow → Netty)</li>
      <li>Pluggable web features: JSON, DB (JPA/Hibernate), Docs, MVC, GraphQL</li>
      <li>Native-image/GraalVM compatibility roadmap</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="mt-6">
      <a href="https://github.com/DoctorDaddySir/PleXionFramework" target="_blank" class="underline hover:text-accent">
        View on GitHub →
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
